post_text:
We are excited to introduce the NEW KEENEYVILLE DISTRICT 20 MOBILE APP! We encourage all of our families + staff to download the free app to your device from the Apple App Store or Google Play Store. Search “Keeneyville District 20” and make sure to turn ON “notifications” by selecting the bell symbol at the top center of the on the “more” tab (bottom right) which will enable you to receive all future push messages from D20. You can also set notifications, sounds, and icon badges through the settings on your own device. For details + instructions go to https://www.esd20.org/district-office/communications-community-relations/d20-mobile-app.

We will continue to communicate with ESD20 staff and families through our usual channels, including emails, recorded phone calls, website, social media (facebook and twitter), as well as the new mobile app.

Starting this week and thru 12/31, D20 can once again offer FREE breakfast and lunch meals to ALL children 18 and under. No paperwork is required, children to not need to be present, and the meals can be picked up by a parent, friend, relative or neighbor on MONDAYS, WEDNESDAYS + FRIDAYS. For School Menus + Pick-up Times/Locations go to https://www.esd20.org/for-parents/food-services

We do still encourage families who may qualify for Free & Reduced Lunch to COMPLETE AN APPLICATION before the October deadline, as it may still be required after 12/31.

post_text:
IMPORTANT TECHNOLOGY MESSAGE - ZOOM: In an effort to improve stability and increase security we made a change to the Google Suite late last night to the Zoom Application. It looks like the replication took longer then expected and hit the district around 12:20pm this afternoon. This change dropped everyone using the Zoom App. We have reversed the change and the Zoom App will be available shortly.

We are seeing that using the website https://zoom.us/ is working, so families may want to consider accessing your Zoom meetings from their website.

Thank you for your patience and understanding.

post_text:
SPRING WOOD MS FAMILIES: We will have a required material pick-up this Friday, August 28th from 9am-2pm. UPDATE: We will also have extended hours on Thursday, August 27 from 2pm to 5:30pm.

During these hours, we ask that all families come to the school for a curbside delivery of school materials that will be needed for instruction. These materials may include art supplies, textbooks, novels, and other curriculum resources. If you are unable to pick up during these hours, we will work with you to make sure these materials are your student's hands by the start of next week. Have a great first week of school!

ESD20 Return to Learn School Supply Lists are READY! Visit https://www.esd20.org/for-parents/school-supply-lists for details. Please note that IN-PERSON STUDENTS and REMOTE STUDENTS will have the same supply list, except that in-person students are required to purchase 3-5 reusable masks. All Skyward systems are now ready for access. Thank you for your patience! All families must submit their Learning Choice in Skyward by this Friday, July 31 at 5pm. PLEASE NOTE: The Learning Choice is NOT A SURVEY. You will be commiting your child to attend In-Person Learning or Enhanced Remote Learning for the first semester.

New and Kindergarten students are not yet in our system, so please contact your school office directly to request that the form be emailed to you. Preschool families do not need to submit a Learning Choice at this time, as the ECC reopening plan will be different and will be released in the coming days.

Keeneyville ESD20

JOIN US for a virtual parent internet safety presentation on Thursday, 5/14 at 6:00pm on Keeping Your Kids Safe Online: Social Media Safety & Awareness, presented by Detective David Chiesa with the DuPage County Sheriff's Office who has extensive experience in internet safety. Please note, that unfortuantely we will not be able to provide translation for this presentation, which will be delivered in English only.

Parents MUST REGISTER ONLINE BY FRIDAY, 5/8, 4PM in order to get the Zoom meeting log-in credentials at https://www.esd20.org/for-parents/parent-groups/parentcafe/registration. We will then email you a link to access the virtual meeting before next Thursday.

post_text: D20 Remote Learning Has Started! We hope that the students enjoyed connecting with their classes as much as the teachers did! Thank you to everyone for your patience and understanding as we adapt to this "new way of teaching and learning!" GIVE KIDS A REASON TO SMILE! As a reminder, a dental examination is required for all Kindergarten + 2nd Grade students. Take advantage of an oportunity to have your child's dental exam completed on GIVE KIDS A SMILE DAY on Friday, Feb. 28th from 9am-2pm which is a non-attendance day for District 20.

Free walk-in dental screenings will be done for children ages 1-18 (no appointment needed) by DuPage County Health Department dentists, at the Central Public Health Center, 111 N. County Farm Rd. in Wheaton. Go to https://www.esd20.org/for-parents/district-20-news for more information.
